title: Area Volleyball: Tigers sweep Spartans
text: Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:05 PM Posted Oct. 22, 2015 at 10:05 PM CAMBRIDGE â€” The ROWVA High School volleyball team swept Ridgewood 25-21, 25-21 on Thursday. Madi Kalb led the Tigers with seven kills and seven digs. Madison Norville added seven kills and a block, Jordan Maher had seven digs, Jasmine Barsema served three aces and Kayla Baumgardner gave out 15 assists for ROWVA. Mollie Shannon had a match best eight kills to lead the Spartans. Shannon also had five digs and two blocks. Also for Ridgewood, Megan Reed made nine digs, Annie Althaus and Mackenzie Coziahr each added seven digs and Coziahr also had two blocks and Catie Helle gave out six assists. Brimfield/Elmwood def. 30-28, 25-21 At Brimfield, the Spartans lost Match 1 in overtime and could not recover. Stephanie Beaird had seven kills to lead Bushnell-Prairie City. Logan Brown had eight digs and 10 service points including a pair of aces. Tiffany Slater added 10 service points and gave out 15 assists and Kayley Peck made three blocks for the Spartans.
